title.narrative: Accelerating Community Engagement and Response on HIV and AIDS Prevention (ACER)

description.narrative: Philippines - HIV - Save the Children Federation, Inc. - STC HQ. This program has the following goals: Maintain prevalence at less than 1 percent in 2020 by preventing the further spread of HIV infection and reducing the impact of the disease on individuals, families, sectors and communities.. The objectives of this program are: By the end of 2020, an improved coverage and linkage of services from prevention and diagnosis among KP to treament and care for PLHIV through intensified delivery of quality and evidence based services.. By the end of 2020, increase in demand and access of KP and public on HIV and STI prevention and care services.. By the end of 2020, a functioning information system is established to aid in planning, monitoring, evaluation and quality assurance of HIV and STI program.. By the end of 2020, a strengthened support system is in place to intensify delivery of quality STI and HIV and aid in addressing barriers on access to services.
